  • Privacy metadata indicating the level of protection required to safeguard potentially stigmatizing information, which if disclosed without authorization, would present a high risk of harm to an individual's reputation and sense of privacy.*Usage Note:* The level of protection afforded restricted confidential information is dictated by specially protective organizational or jurisdictional privacy policies, including at an authorized individual's request, intended to engender patient trust in providers of sensitive services.Privacy policies mandating additional levels of protection by restricting information access preempt less protective privacy policies when the information is used in the delivery and management of healthcare. May be pre-empted by jurisdictional law (e.g., for public health reporting or emergency treatment).Confidentiality code total order hierarchy: Restricted (R) is less protective than *V*, and subsumes all other protection levels (i.e., *N, M, L, and U*).**Examples:** Includes information that is additionally protected such as sensitive conditions mental health, HIV, substance abuse, domestic violence, child abuse, genetic disease, and reproductive health; or sensitive demographic information such as a patient's standing as an employee or a celebrity. May be used to indicate proprietary or classified information that is not related to an individual (e.g., secret ingredients in a therapeutic substance; or the name of a manufacturer). ( src )

AR Autoréfraction An acquisition device, process or method that measures autorefraction.
BDUS Échodensitométrie osseuse An acquisition device, process or method that performs ultrasound bone densitometry.
BI Imagerie biomagnétique An acquisition device, process or method that performs biomagnetic imaging.
BMD Ostéodensitométrie An acquisition device, process or method that performs bone mineral densitometry by X-Ray, including dual-energy X-Ray absorptiometry (DXA) and morphometric X-Ray absorptiometry (MXA).
CR Radiographie assistée par ordinateur An acquisition device, process or method that performs computed radiography.
CT Tomodensitométrie An acquisition device, process or method that performs computed tomography.
DG Diaphanographie An acquisition device, process or method that performs diaphanography.
DMS Dermoscopie An acquisition device, process or method that performs imaging of the surface of the skin using epiluminescence microscopy.
DX Radiographie numérique An acquisition device, process or method that performs digital radiography.
ECG Électrocardiographie An acquisition device, process or method that performs electrocardiography.
EEG Électroencéphalographie An acquisition device, process or method that performs electroencephalography.
EMG Électromyographie An acquisition device, process or method that performs electromyography.
EOG Électrooculographie An acquisition device, process or method that performs electrooculography.
EPS Électrophysiologie cardiaque An acquisition device, process or method that performs cardiac electrophysiology.
ES Endoscopie An acquisition device, process or method that records images during endoscopy.
GM Microscopie générale An acquisition device, process or method that performs general microscopy.
HD Onde hémodynamique An acquisition device, process or method that records hemodynamic waveforms.
IO Radiographie intrabuccale An acquisition device, process or method that performs intra-oral radiography.
IVOCT Tomographie par cohérence optique intravasculaire An acquisition device, process or method that performs intravascular optical coherence tomography
IVUS Ultrasonore intravasculaire An acquisition device, process or method that performs intravascular ultrasound.
KER Kératométrie An acquisition device, process or method that performs keratometry.
LEN Lensométrie An acquisition device, process or method that performs lensometry.
LS Scan laser An acquisition device, process or method that performs laser surface scanning.
MG Mammographie An acquisition device, process or method that performs mammography.
MR Résonance magnétique An acquisition device, process or method that performs magnetic resonance imaging.
NM Médecine nucléaire An acquisition device, process or method that performs nuclear medicine imaging.
OAM Mesures axiales ophtalmiques An acquisition device, process or method that measures the axial length of the eye.
OCT Tomographie à cohérence optique An acquisition device, process or method that uses an interferometric, non-invasive optical tomographic technique to image 2D slices and 3D volumes of tissue using visible and near visible frequencies.
OP Photographique ophtalmique An acquisition device, process or method that performs ophthalmic photography.
OPM Cartographie ophtalmique An acquisition device, process or method that measures corneal topography, corneal or retinal thickness, and other similar parameters that are typically displayed as maps.
OPT Tomographie ophtalmique An acquisition device, process or method that performs tomography of the eye that is based on light and optical principles. Tomography based on other principles, such as ultrasound, is excluded.
OPTBSV Tomographie ophtalmique B-scan analyse de volume An acquisition device, process or method that performs B-scan volume analysis of tomography images of the eye based on light and optical principles. Tomography based on other principles, such as ultrasound, is excluded.
OPTENF Tomographie ophtalmique en face An acquisition device, process or method that creates en face tomography images of the eye based on light and optical principles. Tomography based on other principles, such as ultrasound, is excluded.
OPV Champ visuel ophtalmique An acquisition device, process or method that measures visual fields and perform visual perimetry.
OSS Scanner optique de surface An acquisition device, process or method that performs optical surface scanning.
POS Détecteur de position A device or sensor measuring the orientation of the patient’s body.
PT TEP : Tomographie par émission de positons An acquisition device, process or method that performs positron emission tomography (PET).
PX Panaromique X-Ray An acquisition device, process or method that performs panoramic X-Rays.
RESP Onde respiratoire A device, process or method that produces waveforms of electrical signals from the patient’s respiratory system.
RF Radio-fluoroscopie An acquisition device, process or method that performs radiofluoroscopy.
RG Imagerie radiographique An acquisition device, process or method that performs radiographic imaging (conventional film/screen).
RTIMAGE Image RT An acquisition device, process or method that performs radiotherapy imaging; includes portal imaging.
SM Microscopie à lames An acquisition device, process or method that performs slide microscopy.
SRF Réfraction subjective An acquisition device, process or method that records subjective refraction.
TG Thermographie An acquisition device, process or method that performs thermography.
US Échographie An acquisition device, process or method that performs ultrasound.
VA Acuité visuelle An acquisition device, process or method that measures visual acuity.
XA Angiographie X-Ray An acquisition device, process or method that performs X-Ray angiography.
XC Caméra de photographie externe An acquisition device, process or method that performs photography with an external camera.

113507 Activité administrée The calculated activity at the Radiopharmaceutical Start Time when the radiopharmaceutical is administered to the patient. 113839 E : Dose efficace Effective dose in mSv.
